	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Jagasian wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why is it that new 2600 games use new plastic shells?  Is there that much more money in the 2600 scene than in the NES scene?</div>
<br />
<br />Quite possibly.  The fanbase of that scene has many more years behind it than the NES, so its developers and hobbyists are (likely) on average that much older than those here.  As age tends to beget experience, resources and money, the result translates into higher quality hobby crafts and such.
<br />
<br />So expect the best of the best when the NES hits the 30 year mark! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
