	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Also remember that Atari carts are tiny compared to NES ones, the cart shell and the board.  And they only need one memory chip (and a logic chip).  Compared to NES NROM carts that need 2 memories and some illogic (lockout <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> ).
<br />
<br />Which doesn't make the prototyping cheaper, but does make it easier to make a bunch of them at once.  NES ones will just cost a little more (which is a little multiplied by some crazy quantity for the builder, it becomes a lot).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


